President Trump presented the Commander-in-Chief's Trophy to the Army Black Knights football team for the second year in a row. The President commended the team for their back-to-back victories and their overall success, including winning 21 of their last 26 games and holding the second-longest active winning streak in college football. He also recognized individual players for their outstanding performances, such as quarterback Kelvin Hopkins, who became the first Army player to rush and throw for over 1,000 yards in a single season. The President praised the team's victory in the Army-Navy game and announced plans to consider a waiver for service academy athletes to pursue professional sports before fulfilling their military service commitment. He commended the team for their commitment to serve in the United States Army and thanked them for their selfless dedication to the country. President Trump also discussed the strong state of the military and the administration's efforts to support veterans.